/*
    1. React: 
    
    React is a JS library which is used for building dynamic and scalable web applications using component
    based architecture. Furthermore, it is uses virtual DOM to efficiently update the UI, which minimizes
    direct DOM manipulation and improves performance.


    2. What is React Component ?
    A react component is a self contained class or function which returns JSX which is a part of UI.


    3. What is functional Component?
    A functional component in React is a JS function which returns React Element (JSX), which defines a part 
    of UI in the website.

    It returns React Element, therefore, it is known as functional component.

 
    4. Single Page Application:

    A Single Page Application is a web application that loads a single HTML page and updates content 
    dynamically without reloading the entire page.

    Single page application is an application, where there is only one html file (index.html) and all the 
    changes are done dynamically in this page.

        

    */